  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Create Syria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A call for artists will be designed and launched. Following this, a selection of 15 new generation artists (young non-elite) and 5 established artists (to mentor artists on their artistic practice and advise on community projects). 
The project will also link diaspora activists and artists within communities, via social media.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Create Syria is a collaboration between Ettijihat Independent Culture, the British Council and International Alert to enhance the expertise of artists and cultural activists  located outside of Syria and to empower them to realise their creative projects. The project aims to prevent the drop in artistic production and to provide opportunities for the new generation so that they will be able to develop expertise and links to the preceding generation.  It will also strengthen the value of art as a means to combat the challenges of the prevailing Syrian situation in light of the refugee crisis and the growing frustration it brings. The project will allow artists to collaborate with their peers in the countries in which they live and combat the frustrations that refugees face, including stereotyping, thus supporting resilience of refugee communities.

In light of the political, economic, and cultural changes that Syria is witnessing, the project seeks to create a long-term support network for Syrian artistic production that strengthens contemporary art practices targeting refugees and communities in crisis. It addresses local audiences in the host countries to which artists and new cultural initiatives have moved.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project specific objectives and expected results are:

SO 1: Build the artistic capacity and connectivity of up to 15 established and emerging Syrian artists and CSOs working for social change and peace

SO 2: Engage artists and local refugee and host communities in up to 10  dialogues around relevant social issues through art based practices and creative expression 

SO 3: Facilitate up to 10 new voices and unheard perspectives of the conflict in reaching international community (donors, UN and iNGOs) through a learning and dialogue event

SO 4: Raise the understanding of the value of art and culture in times of crisis in Syria and the region.</narrative>
  </description>
